cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with cross-lingual entity linking, which is a natural language processing task. It may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as entity linking is a common task in information retrieval. Additionally, the paper proposes improvements to entity candidate generation and disambiguation, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also uses experiments to evaluate the proposed model, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with linking named entities to a knowledge base, which is a task related to databases, making cs.DB (Databases) a possible sub-category as well.
